                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">16th-century script</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1500" notAfter="1599"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <desc>
                           Some paleographic features: 
                           ሎ has very often the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line; 
                           መ and ሠ have angular loops; 
                           the bodies of some letters, e.g. የ, ደ, ጸ, and the upper loop of ቆ and ቶ, have a triangular shape; 
                           the left stroke of ዘ is slanted.
                        </desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           Numbers and titles of the psalms.
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r" facs="0003"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText">On the hours of the passion of Jesus Christ</desc>
                           <note>The note begins as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ወጸቦሖ፡ ተማከሩ፡ ሊቃነ፡ ካህናት፡ ይስቅልዎ፡ ለኢየሱ<supplied reason="omitted">ስ</supplied>፡ ወሶበ፡ ጸብሐ፡ ተማከሩ፡ ሊቃነ፡ ካህናት፡ ሐመይዎ፡ ለኢየሱስ፡</q>, 
                              and terminates as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">
                                 ርድአነ፡ ንትቀነይ፡ ለከ፡ ዘእ<supplied reason="omitted">ን</supplied>በለ፡ ድካም፡ ወሀኬት፡ ወትረ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፡ ወ<supplied reason="omitted">በ</supplied>ኵሉ፡ ሰዓት። 
                                 በአሐዱ፡ ወልድከ፡ ዘ<supplied reason="omitted">ቦ</supplied>ቱ፡</q>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#1v" facs="0004"/>
                           <desc type="Supplication">Prayer to God</desc>
                           <note>The note begins as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">
                            ከመ፡ ታድኅነነ፡ እግዚኦ፡ እምዕለት፡ እኪት፡ ወእምሰዓታተ፡ መንሱት፡</q>, and terminates as follows: 
                              <q xml:lang="gez">
                                 ርድአነ፡ ንትቀነይ፡ ለከ፡ ዘእ<supplied reason="omitted">ን</supplied>በለ፡ ድካም፡ ወሀኬት፡ ወትረ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፡ ወ<supplied reason="omitted">በ</supplied>ኵሉ፡ ሰዓት። 
                                 በአሐዱ፡ ወልድከ፡ ዘ<supplied reason="omitted">ቦ</supplied>ቱ፡
                              </q>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#161v" facs="0164"/>
                           <desc type="Doxology">Short praise to Our Lady Mary</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              እሴብሕ፡ ፀጋኪ፡ ኦእግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ ኀጻኒትየ፡ ከመ፡ እም፡ ህየንተ፡ ሐሊብ፡ በነሲአ፡ ስጋ፡ ወደም። 
                                 <sic>ያቍመነ፡</sic>
                               በየማን፡ ምስለ፡ ዓባግዒሁ፡ 
                              ቡሩካን፡ በደብረ፡ ጽዮን፡ መካን። እምይእዜ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ ኣሜን፡ 
                           </q>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#162r" facs="0164"/>
                           <desc type="ScribalSupplication">Supplication to the readers</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዘገብረ፡ ኤዎስጣቴዎስ፡ ኢትርግምዎ፡ እለ፡ ርኢክምዎ፡</q>
                           <note>The note is written in the upper margin of the leaf, in the same hand as <ref target="#a3">the praise to Our Lady Mary</ref>. 
                              It mentions <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11292Ewostat">ʾEwosṭātewos</persName> as the scribe of the note.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#186r" facs="0188"/>
                           <desc type="MagicText">Magic prayer</desc>
                           <note>The note is mostly erased. It begins as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">
                              መ<del rend="erasure">...</del>ን፡ መፍዝዝ፡ መቅዝዝ፡ መቅዝዝ፡ ወኀይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ </q>, and terminates as follows: 
                              <q xml:lang="gez">ዘእንበለ፡ 
                                    <sic>ሰለም፡</sic>
                                    <sic>አገሌ፡</sic>
                                  ለገብርከ።</q>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark of the Vatican Library <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 14 | Aethiop.</q> is written on the cover, together with the coat of arms 
                              of pope <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7893PiusIX">Pius IX</persName>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>The title of the book <q xml:lang="la">Psalmi Dapid</q> is written in a <date>17th-century</date> hand on a fragment of paper glued at the beginning of the manuscript, 
                              together with the shelfmark of the Vatican Library <q xml:lang="la">Ath. 14</q> written in a recent hand.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
